parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized shoulder harness can lead to inadequate restraint, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The motorized shoulder harness intermittently locks up too tightly
fails to move upward and restrain the driver
disengages if the door is opened while driving
over-retracts and twists into the track
and fails to disconnect on driver/passenger.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to tighten excessively, making it difficult or impossible to release, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The driver-side seat belt retractor tightens up and won't release
the seat belt fails to retract
and the passenger's passive restraint ceases to engage midway.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling and locking of the engine can cause loss of power and control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while driving at any speed
the vehicle is unable to restart
the engine shows no signs of oil leakage before locking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic safety harness can compromise the safety of the driver and passengers, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The driver's side automatic safety harness does not work
the harness does not retract or extend properly
the harness is stuck in a fixed position
the harness does not respond to electrical signals.
